dhcp_option_help="<b>DHCP Option</b></p><p>An additional DHCP option can be used to exchange some useful information between the DHCP server and DHCP client. It can also be used to obtain configuration parameters from the DHCP server.</p><p><b>Vendor Class Identifier String (Option 60)</b></p><p>This option is used by DHCP clients to identify itself to the DHCP server while performing a 4-way handshake. Enter the vendor class identifier string, as indicated by your Internet service provider (ISP). If your ISP did not provide you with a vendor class identifier string, leave this field blank.</p><p><b>Client Identifier String (Option 61)</b></p><p>This option is used by DHCP clients to specify a unique client identifier while performing a 4-way handshake. Enter the client identifier string, as indicated by your Internet service provider (ISP). If your ISP did not provide you with a client identifier string, leave this field blank."
